\section sec_intro_what What is KAPSEL?
- \b KAPSEL stands for "Kyoto Advanced Particle Simulator for Electro - 
  hydrodynamics" based on a direct numerical simulation method for colloidal
  dispersions called \b SPM (Smoothed Profile Method). Kapsel enables us to
  simulate dynamics of solid particles dispersed in simple and complex fluids.
  Kapsel enables us to simulate complex rheological properties of colloidal
  dispersions, electrophoresis of charged colloids, etc.
- \b KAPSEL-2 is the latest version fo KAPSEL. It can introduce thermal
  fluctuations to the system and also perform rheology simulations under 
  steady sheare or oscillatory shear flow being fully compatible with usual
  periodic boundary conditions. Computational efficiency is also much improved
  from the original version so that one can simulate larger systems.
- \b KAPSEL is a software free to use. To download and use KAPSEL, one must 
  agree with the \ref page_license "KAPSEL license agreement".

